attributes.background:
Jobseekers need help at all steps of the job search and at present are not automatically receiving it.  Often, they do not receive it even if they ask for help.

Jobseekers need to automatically receive help and advice in:

Where to search for jobs (such as a list of websites);

How to gain experience and move forward in a career;

Writing a CV;

Filling in application forms, and;

Interview techniques.

At present, they are supposed to receive this help from the jobcentre, but members of staff take the attitude that you cannot be choosy and should go for any job available, usually a low-skilled job, presumably to reduce their statistics.  The above suggestions would reduce the length of time people are on jobseekers allowance anyway.
